9:
Yeah. She's been glued to the World 
Flipper doing checks and maintenance.
12:
After seeing the masked girl summon 
Orochi with a World Flipper, I suppose 
I can hardly blame Stella for her 
caution.
21:
Oh, I wasn't expecting such a welcome 
party. 
Could you tell I was coming?
27:
It has been a while. 
I trust you've been in good health?
31:
Yes, but gosh, 
you gave us a good scare. 
Why the sudden visit?
34:
A simple test of Yamato's World Flipper, 
as it IS under my jurisdiction.
35:
The Diviners' Commission thanks you 
for your assistance, Stella. 
We could not have recovered it 
ourselves.
42:
The synchronization.
Our World Flipper has been running 
continuously ever since.
44:
Any layman could walk straight 
through to another world. Honestly, 
it's as troublesome as it is convenient.
47:
I assure you, 
however, the Commission is taking 
the utmost care to guard it. 
You need not worry about unwanted 
visitors.
51:
I can think of a few foxes who'd be all 
too excited to sneak through...
54:
You said you were just testing the 
World Flipper out, Suizen. 
Do you have time for a chat, or were 
you going to head straight back?
56:
I have a matter to discuss with you, 
actually.
58:
As Chair of the Diviners' Commission, 
I, Gogyou Suizen, would like to propose 
an alliance.
62:
Stella, Light, Alk. As the representatives 
of Starview Village, would you agree to 
enter a pact with the Diviners' 
Commission?
71:
As you are well aware, Yamato is 
comprised of two merged worlds—
the Yamato of the East, and the 
Yamato of the West.
73:
The Commission endeavors to 
understand the merge's cause, as well 
as alleviate the confusion and chaos it 
brought about.
75:
In our haste, we played right into the 
Grand Diviner—that masked woman's 
plans, but... Our true goal still stands.
79: Did she know what caused the merge?
82:
I believe so, yes.
I would not be surprised if she caused 
it herself.
84:
Your fates are closely intertwined with 
hers, leading me to believe you may be 
instrumental in exposing the truth.
88:
I see. 
You wish us to provide intelligence.
91:
Put simply, yes. 
In exchange, I offer my services as the 
Commission's most powerful diviner. 
Ask, and I shall lend you my full 
support!
96:
That's a dramatic way to say you want 
to join the party.
99:
We'd never say no to some extra help, 
right Stella?
103:
Of course. 
Welcome to Starview Village, Suizen.
108:
You may not do anything 
as rash as before.
112:
Yes... 
I more than learned my lesson.
116:
Hello, Suizen. 
You've come to browse the library?
120:
Yes, I find reading a highly efficient 
means to obtain information.
123:
You have quite an assortment here 
though, I must say. 
Picture books, fantasy novels, and... Is 
this—? You have manga?
126:
We shelves books from friends in many 
worlds. I can hardly believe how much 
the collection has grown.
129:
In that case, I will look into transferring 
some of the Commission's collection 
over. It may prove useful.
132:
...Stella. Stella, please allow me to be 
blunt—
134:
You are almost identical to the masked 
woman we saw, and claim to be the 
"Keeper" of the World Flipper. 
Who are you, really?
138:
For as long as I can remember, 
I was always here watching over the 
stars—the worlds—by myself.
140:
That's all I ever did until Alk and Light 
came.
142:
Maybe some part of me is broken... 
Malfunctioning?
146:
You have my deepest apologies, Stella. 
I did not wish to doubt you, but I could 
not help but ask.
149:
I don't mind. I would also like to know 
who that woman was—and who I am.
152:
I promise you, I shall aid and protect 
you in your pursuit of the truth.
154:
There is one answer I can provide you 
now.
157:
You are neither broken nor 
malfunctioning.
160:
If anything, you were the one who got 
me back on my feet after I broke down.
163: I-it wasn't only me. Inaho helped too.
167:
Yes, you're right. 
Ahaha, I suppose I owe her too.
